The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | 4 lakh for kin
                                                                                                               4 lakh for kin
                            
	Calcutta, June 3: Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee today said he would meet the Prime Minister in Delhi on June 19 to discuss cyclone relief and announced that the state would match the Centres ex-gratia of Rs 2 lakh for the kin of those killed.         
	The families of the dead will now get Rs 4 lakh each, the chief minister said.        
	An 11-member central team will soon visit the cyclone-hit districts to see the ex- tent of damage. I am happy with the Centres quick response to the plight of the people affected by the cyclone, Bhattacharjee added.                                                                                                                                                                              
